"{\"uid\": \"aa.com.tr-en-europe-french-rail-network-restored-after-sabotage-disrupts-olympic-travel-3288203\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"T\\u00fcrkiye  World  Middle East  Americas  Europe  Africa  Asia - Pacific  Economy  Politics  Energy  Sports  Infographics  Opinion  Photo  Video  Environment  Education  Life  Culture  Opinion  Health  Science-Technology  Business News  Finance Terminal  Anadolu Images  Energy Terminal  AA Academy  Green Line  Discrimination Line  Fact Check Line  Career AA  Corporate News    ANKARA  France's high-speed train network resumed normal operations on Monday, three days after sabotage acts significantly disrupted travel ahead of the Olympics opening ceremony, according to the transport minister, the press reports said on Monday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 627, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Patrice Vergriete confirmed that the coordinated arson attacks on Friday morning targeted key points of the rail infrastructure, according to local media outlets.\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The incidents raised concerns as they occurred just before the grand opening.\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, authorities have yet to determine the perpetrators or whether the timing was intended to disrupt the event.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Metro disruptions in Paris  In Paris, where the number of tourists is expected to reach 16 million during the Olympic Games, there were also disruptions to metro services.\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999302688163, \"rank\": 6.973115143017903e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999302688163, \"rank\": 6.973115143017903e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to an announcement on X by Paris' 8th metro line, services were disrupted at the Opera station due to police intervention.\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999302688163, \"rank\": 6.973115143017903e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reason for the intervention was not disclosed.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The line is used by visitors and tourists wanting to attend Olympic events.\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to France Bleu, a network of local and regional radio stations in France, services on the Paris 13th metro line, which connects Paris to the suburb of Saint-Denis, were suspended between 12.52 p.m. and 2.30 p.m. local time (1052-1230GMT) due to a serious passenger accident.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1440, \"end\": 1451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"France Bleu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\"}, {\"begin\": 1440, \"end\": 1451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"France Bleu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\"}, {\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995272863351854, \"rank\": 0.0002500015568853878, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999302688163, \"rank\": 6.973115143017903e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1565, \"end\": 1570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999302688163, \"rank\": 6.973115143017903e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Denis_station\", \"score\": 0.9993758896506054, \"rank\": 0.0005756356468677512, \"text\": \"Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Denis_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Denis_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Six metro cars were stuck in tunnels and passengers in three of the cars disembarked, walking along the metro tracks to the nearest station.\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"History  Editorial Guidelines  Social Media Policies  Executive Team  Domestic Offices  International Offices  Logos  Communication  RSS  Subscription Requests  Announcement Service  Quality Management  Privacy and Cookies Policy  Information Policy  Diary  Business News  Finance Terminal  Anadolu Images  Energy Terminal  AA Academy  Green Line  Discrimination Line  Fact Check Line  IPhone Application  IPad Application  Android Application\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": []}]}"